The paper discusses techniques for compressing indexes for highly repetitive document collections, which is a topic closely related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of indexing solutions, which falls under the category of databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses natural language processing techniques, such as stemming and stop-word removal, which are relevant to computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses experimental results and parameter tuning, which are topics related to machine learning (cs.LG).
